{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781150566081,"sessionID":"ses_14b28450fffeXtSj4IYMHTa90z","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_YeqjUAM2EVqDLTsc4kXcDNET","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"causal|BFS|breadth|traversal|memory_drift_why|causal_edges","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/012-causal-traversal-bfs","include":"*.md"},"output":"Found 66 matches\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/012-causal-traversal-bfs/tasks.md:\n  Line 2: title: \"Tasks: Causal Traversal BFS Read Path [template:level_1/tasks.md]\"\n\n  Line 5:   - \"012-causal-traversal-bfs tasks\"\n\n  Line 10:     packet_pointer: \"system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/012-causal-traversal-bfs\"\n\n  Line 13:     recent_action: \"All traversal replacement tasks completed and verified\"\n\n  Line 19:       session_id: \"scaffold-012-causal-traversal-bfs\"\n\n  Line 26: # Tasks: Causal Traversal BFS Read Path\n\n  Line 50: - [x] T001 Capture live-DB fixture (edges at measured scale, degree distribution). Evidence: new vitest fixture uses 10,240 causal edges, max degree 20, seeds 5, hops 2.\n\n  Line 51: - [x] T002 Equivalence harness: record current CTE outputs as snapshots. Evidence: `causal-traversal-bfs-equivalence.vitest.ts` compares current CTE output to BFS output exactly.\n\n  Line 52: - [x] T003 [P] Traversal helper: hop-capped weighted walk mode. Evidence: `collectCausalWeightedNeighbors` in `lib/graph/bfs-traversal.ts`.\n\n  Line 60: - [x] T004 [P] Traversal helper: directed unbounded reachability mode. Evidence: `collectDependencyReachability` in `lib/graph/bfs-traversal.ts`.\n\n  Line 70: - [x] T007 Equivalence suite green across fixtures. Evidence: `npx vitest run tests/causal-traversal-bfs-equivalence.vitest.ts --reporter verbose` passed 4/4 tests.\n\n  Line 71: - [x] T008 Latency benchmark vs CTE recorded. Evidence: fixture_edges=10240, max_degree=20, seeds=5, hops=2, CTE=1.429ms, BFS=1.117ms.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/012-causal-traversal-bfs/implementation-summary.md:\n  Line 3: description: \"Shipped causal traversal BFS read path: shared BFS helper replaces recursive CTE traversal consumers, with exact equivalence and latency evidence.\"\n\n  Line 5:   - \"012-causal-traversal-bfs summary\"\n\n  Line 10:     packet_pointer: \"system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/012-causal-traversal-bfs\"\n\n  Line 13:     recent_action: \"Shared BFS traversal helper shipped with equivalence and latency tests\"\n\n  Line 17:       - \".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/graph/bfs-traversal.ts\"\n\n  Line 18:       - \".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/search/causal-boost.ts\"\n\n  Line 20:       - \".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/causal-traversal-bfs-equivalence.vitest.ts\"\n\n  Line 23:       session_id: \"ship-012-causal-traversal-bfs\"\n\n  Line 24:       parent_session_id: \"scaffold-012-causal-traversal-bfs\"\n\n  Line 28:       - \"BFS cutover proceeded after exact CTE equivalence passed in test.\"\n\n  Line 43: | **Spec Folder** | 012-causal-traversal-bfs |\n\n  Line 54: Shipped one shared app-level BFS traversal module for the two recursive traversal read paths in the memory backend.\n\n  Line 56: ### Shared BFS Helper\n\n  Line 58: `mcp_server/lib/graph/bfs-traversal.ts` now exposes two production modes:\n\n  Line 60: - `collectCausalWeightedNeighbors(database, seeds, maxHops, relationWeights)`: hop-capped weighted undirected walk for causal neighbor boosts. It uses separate indexed source and target reads per hop and preserves independent per-node min-hop and max-walk-score aggregation.\n\n  Line 65: - `mcp_server/lib/search/causal-boost.ts`: `getNeighborBoosts` now calls the BFS helper; the recursive CTE was removed from production source.\n\n  Line 66: - `mcp_server/lib/storage/memo.ts`: `collectDependents` and cycle checks now call the directed reachability helper. The store caches dependency edge count at construction and skips traversal queries for the first insert when `dependency_edges` is empty.\n\n  Line 72: | `mcp_server/tests/causal-traversal-bfs-equivalence.vitest.ts` | Exact CTE-vs-BFS equivalence, call-site behavior, zero-row fast path, and benchmark coverage |\n\n  Line 80: The helper was implemented as a generic BFS core plus SQLite readers. For causal boosts, the reader avoids the old recursive join with `source_id = node OR target_id = node` by querying source and target directions separately. For memo storage, the directed reader walks `dependency_edges` from parent to child and returns sorted output at the call site to preserve the prior result order.\n\n  Line 82: The equivalence test kept the old recursive SQL in the test file only. It compares BFS output against current CTE output exactly for node membership, seed exclusion, per-node minimum hop, maximum walk score, and relation/strength weighting. A floating-point multiplication-order mismatch was caught by the test and fixed by matching SQLite's left-to-right multiplication order.\n\n  Line 105: | `npx vitest run tests/causal-traversal-bfs-equivalence.vitest.ts --reporter verbose` | PASS, 1 file, 4 tests |\n\n  Line 106: | `npx vitest run tests/causal-boost.vitest.ts tests/memo-storage.vitest.ts` | PASS, 2 files, 9 tests |\n\n  Line 113: The new suite passed exact equality for BFS output against the current recursive CTE output on a live-shaped fixture:\n\n  Line 115: - Fixture: 10,240 causal edges, max degree 20, 5 seeds, 2 hops.\n\n  Line 123: | Fixture Edges | Max Degree | Seeds | Hops | Recursive CTE Mean | BFS Mean |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/012-causal-traversal-bfs/spec.md:\n  Line 2: title: \"Feature Specification: Causal Traversal BFS Read Path [template:level_1/spec.md]\"\n\n  Line 3: description: \"Replace the two recursive-CTE graph traversals with a shared app-level BFS helper: the current CTE join condition defeats index use, and the memo path queries empty tables on every insert.\"\n\n  Line 5:   - \"causal traversal bfs\"\n\n  Line 7:   - \"neighbor boost traversal\"\n\n  Line 13:     packet_pointer: \"system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/012-causal-traversal-bfs\"\n\n  Line 16:     recent_action: \"Shared BFS traversal helper shipped and verified\"\n\n  Line 22:       session_id: \"scaffold-012-causal-traversal-bfs\"\n\n  Line 29: # Feature Specification: Causal Traversal BFS Read Path\n\n  Line 62: The only two WITH RECURSIVE consumers in the memory backend are read paths with measurable inefficiencies. getNeighborBoosts (lib/search/causal-boost.ts:431) recurses with ON ce.source_id = cw.node_id OR ce.target_id = cw.node_id, which prevents single-index use on every hop; the live graph measured 10,240 causal edges with max degree 22, so an indexed two-query-per-hop BFS is estimated at 0.5-2ms - at or below the CTE. collectDependents (lib/storage/memo.ts:192) runs an unbounded recursive CTE and wouldCreateCycle fires per insert, yet dependency_edges and memoization_records both held zero rows when measured (2026-06-10). Source evidence: z_future/sqlite-to-turso research.md gap 6 and 004 - gap-alternatives.md section 4.\n\n  Line 65: One shared, snapshot-equivalence-tested BFS traversal helper serves both call sites, removing the recursive-SQL dependency while making the hot read path faster and the dormant memo path effectively free.\n\n  Line 74: - Shared traversal helper (hop-capped weighted walk + directed unbounded reachability modes)\n\n  Line 88: | `mcp_server/lib/search/causal-boost.ts` | Modify | getNeighborBoosts uses the BFS helper |\n\n  Line 90: | `mcp_server/lib/graph/` (new traversal helper) | Create | Shared BFS module with both traversal modes |\n\n  Line 103: | REQ-001 | BFS output is equivalence-tested against the current CTE output on a live-DB fixture (per-node MIN hop, MAX walk_score, seeds excluded, relation weighting) | Equivalence suite green; any divergence is a test failure, not a tolerance |\n\n  Line 118: - **SC-001**: BFS replaces both recursive CTEs with zero retrieval-behavior change (equivalence suite green).\n\n  Line 119: - **SC-002**: Hot-path traversal p95 at or below current CTE on the live-size fixture.\n\n  Line 130: | Dependency | Phase 003 touches causal write paths | Low | This phase is read-path only; coordinate merge order with 003 children |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/012-causal-traversal-bfs/plan.md:\n  Line 2: title: \"Implementation Plan: Causal Traversal BFS Read Path [template:level_1/plan.md]\"\n\n  Line 3: description: \"Build one shared BFS traversal helper (hop-capped weighted walk + directed unbounded reachability), prove output equivalence against the two recursive CTEs on a live-DB fixture, then cut both call sites over with empty-table fast paths.\"\n\n  Line 5:   - \"012-causal-traversal-bfs plan\"\n\n  Line 10:     packet_pointer: \"system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/012-causal-traversal-bfs\"\n\n  Line 13:     recent_action: \"Plan executed; BFS helper replaces recursive traversal consumers\"\n\n  Line 19:       session_id: \"scaffold-012-causal-traversal-bfs\"\n\n  Line 26: # Implementation Plan: Causal Traversal BFS Read Path\n\n  Line 52: Build one shared BFS traversal helper (hop-capped weighted walk + directed unbounded reachability), prove output equivalence against the two recursive CTEs on a live-DB fixture, then cut both call sites over with empty-table fast paths.\n\n  Line 80: - **Traversal helper (lib/graph)**: Both BFS modes; pure functions over an edge reader\n\n  Line 81: - **Equivalence harness**: CTE-vs-BFS snapshot comparison on fixtures\n\n  Line 84: causal-boost/memo call sites -> traversal helper -> two indexed flat queries per hop -> merged results identical to CTE output.\n\n  Line 138: | Phase 003 (causal write lifecycle) | Internal | Pending | Coordinate merge order; read-path only here |\n","metadata":{"matches":66,"truncated":false},"title":"causal|BFS|breadth|traversal|memory_drift_why|causal_edges","time":{"start":1781150566061,"end":1781150566080}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_090de10123b02aa1016a2a3365e3f08191bb49d1ffa6ab6b19"}},"id":"prt_eb4d8c67d001GM7caFseC6pYRq","sessionID":"ses_14b28450fffeXtSj4IYMHTa90z","messageID":"msg_eb4d89bd70019GBzQ1oIXhbLs2"}}
